A man was robbed in a Manhattan subway station by a trio of thieves who shoved him to the platform, police said. The victim, 60, was walking on the southbound A/C/E platform at West 42nd Street and Eighth Avenue, beneath the Port Authority Bus Terminal, when two men and a woman allegedly approached and pushed him to the floor, according to an NYPD spokeswoman. The three alleged attackers threatened the man, took his phone and fled, NYPD said. The victim refused medical attention. No arrests have been made.